                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-danger">Deferred</span>Define additional Finance data requirements for Phase 2 <em>(needs input from owner)</em></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Phase 1d – CS Live Help Overhaul -->
                    <div class="mb-5">
                        <h6 class="text-uppercase fw-semibold mb-3 border-bottom pb-2">
                            <i class="bx bx-support me-1"></i>Phase 1d – CS Live Help Overhaul (Kanban + AM Requests)
                            <span class="badge bg-warning text-dark ms-2">In Progress</span>
                        </h6>
                        <div class="alert alert-secondary py-2 mb-3 small">
                            <strong>Context:</strong> Brand new feature — AMs (external) submit support requests via a Kanban board; CS agents work, respond, and escalate them.
                            Built for high volume (hundreds–thousands/day) using <strong>SignalR push diffs</strong> + duty-cycle archiving.
                            Which CS agents are active on the board is driven by Work Distribution — agents allocated to a CS Live Help slot are considered "on duty".
                            The Work Distribution and duty schedule systems are <strong>not modified</strong>.
                        </div>

                        <p class="fw-semibold mb-2">Architecture Decisions</p>
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-info text-dark">Decided</span>Real-time: <strong>SignalR</strong> — push diffs only (CardAdded / CardUpdated / CardDeleted / CommentAdded)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-info text-dark">Decided</span>Board columns: cursor/keyset pagination — top 50 cards, load-more via AJAX</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-info text-dark">Decided</span>Duty cycle: configurable via <code>appsettings.json</code> — default: run every <strong>6 h</strong>, archive <code>Completed</code> cards older than <strong>3 days</strong></li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-info text-dark">Decided</span>Duplicate prevention: AMs see each other's open requests (read-only). Warning if same brand + type already open</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-info text-dark">Decided</span>Security: AMs treated as untrusted; input sanitised, English-only on "Other" field, rate-limited</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="fw-semibold mb-2">1d-i – Data Models &amp; Migration</p>
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>Create <code>CsRequest</code> model (AM, Brand, RequestType, Status enum, CustomDescription, timestamps)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>Create <code>CsRequestType</code> lookup (Simulate POI, Reset Password, Other…)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>Create <code>CsRequestComment</code> model (thread per card, <code>IsSystemMessage</code> flag)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>Create <code>CsRequestArchive</code> table (mirror of CsRequest for archived completed records)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>Create <code>AmAuditLog</code> table (UserId, Action, EntityId, Timestamp, IP)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>Add DB indexes on Status, CreatedAt, BrandId, AccountManagerId</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span>EF Core migration <code>Phase1d_CsLiveHelpModels</code> applied</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="fw-semibold mb-2">1d-ii – AM Request Actions (external-facing)</p>
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span><code>GET /CsLiveHelp/Requests</code> — AM Kanban (own cards) + read-only "Others" column (same-brand duplicate guard)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span><code>POST /CsLiveHelp/CreateRequest</code> — Brand + RequestType dropdown (incl. "Other") + English-only text (max 500 chars)</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span><code>POST /CsLiveHelp/EditRequest/{id}</code> — AM edits own <em>Open</em> cards only</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span><code>POST /CsLiveHelp/DeleteRequest/{id}</code> — AM deletes own <em>Open</em> cards only</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center gap-2 px-0"><span class="badge bg-success">Done</span><code>POST /CsLiveHelp/AddComment/{id}</code> — AM adds comment to own request thread</li>
                        </ul>

